    "title": "AI & Robotics Snacks — April 22, 2026",
    "date": "2026-04-22",
    "tags": ["NVIDIA GR00T N1.7", "Cursor $50B valuation", "SoundHound LivePerson", "OpenAI MCP Enterprise"],
    "fresh": true,
    "content": "**AI & Robotics Snacks** — April 22, 2026\n\n---\n\n## 🦾 NVIDIA Open-Sourced a 3B-Param Robot Brain. It Runs on a Gaming GPU.\n\nNVIDIA released GR00T N1.7 in early access — a 3-billion-parameter Vision-Language-Action model for humanoid robots, commercially licensed under Apache 2.0. It uses a Cosmos-Reason2-2B reasoning backbone with a 32-layer Diffusion Transformer for motor control, trained on 20,000 hours of EgoScale human video data.\n\n- **The deployment:** 16GB+ VRAM for inference — an RTX 4090, L40, or H100 will do. Runs on Jetson AGX Thor for in-robot deployment. Apache 2.0 means commercial shipping with zero royalties.\n- **The ambition:** NVIDIA is positioning GR00T as the \"Android of humanoid robots\" — an open foundation model that manufacturers build on top of rather than training from scratch.\n\n*NVIDIA just open-sourced the brain for humanoid robots. The robots are still slow, expensive, and mostly in labs. The software is ready.*\n\n**Sources:** [NVIDIA Developer](https://developer.nvidia.com/isaac/gr00t) | [HuggingFace](https://huggingface.co/blog/nvidia/gr00t-n1-7)\n\n---\n\n## 💰 Cursor Is Raising $2B at a $50B Valuation. NVIDIA Is Joining the Round.\n\nAI code editor Cursor is in talks to close a $2B round at a $50B+ valuation — nearly double its $29.3B valuation from six months ago. Andreessen Horowitz and Thrive Capital lead; NVIDIA is also joining. The round is already oversubscribed.\n\n- **The numbers:** $2B in annualized recurring revenue as of February 2026, with a $6B ARR projection by year-end — 3x growth in 10 months from a product that is essentially a code editor with a chat window.\n- **The trajectory:** $900M round in June 2025 → $2.3B at $29.3B in November 2025 → $2B+ at $50B+ in April 2026. Three fundraises in ten months. The market is pricing this as AI infrastructure, not a productivity tool.\n\n*Cursor raised at $29.3B six months ago. Now $50B. Next round will probably have a \"T\" in it.*\n\n**Sources:** [CNBC](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/04/19/cursor-ai-2-billion-funding-round.html) | [TechCrunch](https://techcrunch.com/2026/04/17/sources-cursor-in-talks-to-raise-2b-at-50b-valuation-as-enterprise-growth-surges/)\n\n---\n\n## 🎙️ SoundHound Is Buying LivePerson. Two Companies Squeezed by GPT Become One.\n\nSoundHound AI agreed on April 21 to acquire LivePerson in an all-stock deal with concurrent debt restructuring, creating a debt-free omnichannel conversational AI platform. Combined 2027 revenue target: $350-400M.\n\n- **The logic:** SoundHound brings voice AI (automotive, restaurant, IVR); LivePerson brings text-based customer service AI. Together: one platform across voice and text enterprise deployments, debt-free balance sheet.\n- **The subtext:** Both companies were being squeezed by GPT-5 and Google flooding the enterprise market. Consolidation is the rational response when organic growth gets structurally harder.\n\n*Two conversational AI companies compressed by frontier models decide to become one conversational AI company compressed by frontier models. Bold strategy.*\n\n**Sources:** [TipRanks](https://www.tipranks.com/news/company-announcements/soundhound-ai-to-acquire-liveperson-in-all-stock-deal)\n\n---\n\n## 🔌 OpenAI Added MCP Connectors and an Excel Add-In to ChatGPT Enterprise.\n\nOpenAI rolled out the ability for ChatGPT Enterprise and Team admins to build and deploy custom connectors to proprietary internal systems using the Model Context Protocol (MCP). Separately, a ChatGPT for Excel add-in is now available for enterprise users to run prompts against spreadsheet data directly inside Microsoft's environment.\n\n- **The MCP angle:** MCP lets ChatGPT connect to internal databases, CRMs, and APIs without routing data through OpenAI's servers. Enterprise customers get AI-native access to their own systems without the data sovereignty headache.\n- **The Excel angle:** ChatGPT in Excel is the path to the knowledge workers who still live in spreadsheets — which is most of them. OpenAI is going where the enterprise actually is.\n\n*ChatGPT can now connect to your internal systems and live in your spreadsheets. The enterprise plumbing phase of the AI transition has officially begun.*\n\n**Sources:** [OpenAI](https://help.openai.com/en/articles/11391654-chatgpt-business-release-notes)"
  }
